Class StandStorage

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.storage.AbstractStorage<I,io.spine.server.entity.EntityRecord,RecordReadRequest<I>>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Storage<AggregateStateId,io.spine.server.entity.EntityRecord,RecordReadRequest<AggregateStateId>>, StorageWithLifecycleFlags<AggregateStateId,io.spine.server.entity.EntityRecord,RecordReadRequest<AggregateStateId>>, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    @SPI
public abstract class StandStorage
extends RecordStorage<AggregateStateId>
    Serves as a storage for the latest Aggregate states.

    Used by an instance of Stand to optimize the Aggregate state fetch performance.

    See Also:
    Any.getTypeUrl(), Stand

      • readAll

        public java.util.Iterator<io.spine.server.entity.EntityRecord> readAll(EntityQuery<AggregateStateId> query,
                                                                       com.google.protobuf.FieldMask fieldMask)
        Reads all the state records from the storage.

        This method overrides the behaviour of the superclass. Since StandStorage does not support Entity Columns, the passed EntityQuery does not affect the resulting Map in any way.

        Calling this method is equivalent to calling readAll(fieldMask).

        Overrides:
        readAll in class RecordStorage<AggregateStateId>
        Parameters:
        query - ignored
        fieldMask - the fields to retrieve
        Returns:
        all the records with the FieldMask applied
        See Also:
        RecordStorage.readAll(FieldMask)
